entries.femaleVariant: V?
Call me Teddy. Get in. I'll give you the brief.
All right, Teddy. Time to get to work.
Just do your ninja stuff, heh. And don't get caught on camera.
You know their security?
You know your way around their security?
Oh-ho, I like you. You want detes, Teddy's got detes. Here's the deal – two cams, five guards. And another three in the back.
Oof, lookin' a little green at the gills, but hey, I get it, it won't be easy. Just do whatcha can to keep that mug off camera, got it?
Cameras love me, not you. I'll be in touch.
Sure. See what I can do.
One and only. You Ted?
[Get in] Fine, Teddy.
[Get in] Sort of in a rush here.
Fine, Teddy, what's the sich?
You get in the garage and place this tracker under the truck. Just... just watch out for surveillance cams.
You are makin' my career, right here, V! The soldier of truth!
See that garage on the left? Belongs to Kendachi. Tip came in they've got special goods sitting in there.
Special?
For the 6th Street gang.
OK. So What do I have to do?
Why do you care?
Kendachi and the gang are in cahoots. Who cares?
Who cares? Jesus. What has this world come to? Listen.
On one side you've got the patriots – real salt o' the earth – ex-military, second amendment nuts.
And on the other – Kendachi. Clean, pure as snow megacorp. Ideology and race-wise.
Shady dealin' 'tween the two? Ah, that's a story.
Wait, you're doing a piece?
I get it. You want a scandal.
Wait, you're doin' a piece about this?
I get it. You want a scandal.
Oh, it is gonna be huge, I'm tellin' ya. And guess who stands to gain the most?
Public opinion – if the story gets out. If it devolves into blackmail – News 54. And if devolves further, then just little ol' me.
I dunno, who?
I want the truth – period. Especially if it's inconvenient.
Piece o' cake.
So, what's on me to do?
[Place tracker]
What do I do?
[Get out]
[Take tracker] All right. Let's do this.
